<sec id="id-2dcfa45b-9c82-4b43-e068-f4a898796c0a"><title><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="6861742" change-id="efdf7099-cea0-4106-9d12-7364db05bf54" text="A.1 " timestamp="1633434319764"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f95bbcb2-779f-4969-bf19-7f38a52ff94a" timestamp="1627510163021"?>User requirements of specific LET needs pertaining to privacy issues<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f95bbcb2-779f-4969-bf19-7f38a52ff94a"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="6861742" change-id="91eea3c1-f1c2-4d61-da2e-337dc3812e3e" text="Based on Annex E.3 in 36N1737" timestamp="1633273283223"?></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="2a95736f-e367-4e60-e034-3c7203469d95" timestamp="1627510187815"?>LET provided by public sector organizations receives a high degree of privacy protection under legislation<xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-79a338e9-301e-4949-bdd4-2ee3c371043c.xml#id-b27ca9c0-a3d9-4798-fec3-b0076c9e04a2" id="id-54ce2a5f-44a4-4261-b189-e2bbf676296d" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-b27ca9c0-a3d9-4798-fec3-b0076c9e04a2"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2a95736f-e367-4e60-e034-3c7203469d95"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="830322a0-d2c7-434e-ecb2-d22a9f76dae8" timestamp="1633273291838"?>Based on Annex E.3 in 36N1737<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="830322a0-d2c7-434e-ecb2-d22a9f76dae8"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6e6198af-9045-498b-d8c6-0209234adde6" timestamp="1627510187815"?></p></fn>. Privacy protection is “IT-neutral”, i.e. it pertains to the recorded information on or about an identifiable individual irrespective of the information and communications technologies (ICT) used, i.e., whether recorded or managed in digital or non-digital form;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6e6198af-9045-498b-d8c6-0209234adde6"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="a731ec9e-446e-40a0-e5bb-ee04d2b27db2" timestamp="1627510202636"?><list-item id="id-2c699dba-ec84-4640-97f3-28f1483a4c44"><p>personal information regarding students/learners who are “minors” requires added particular/special privacy/data protection. Within Canada, the “default” age of a minor is less than 18 years of age<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a731ec9e-446e-40a0-e5bb-ee04d2b27db2"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="7671038" change-id="6502c87d-7694-462d-a802-02fca0212375" text="The definition of age of majority, i.e., when an individual is considered to be a “minor” varies within Canadian jurisdictional domains at both the federal and provincial/territorial levels of jurisdictional domains. It also varies with respect to rights and responsibilities of both (1) the individual; and, (2) those of its parent(s) or guardian(s)." timestamp="1644576411181"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="053e2885-627e-4ec4-9fc8-4a950065c4ca" timestamp="1627510202636"?><xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-79a338e9-301e-4949-bdd4-2ee3c371043c.xml#id-233b7b4b-69d5-40ee-c53c-f22134bfb2c2" id="id-f20d0a64-082d-4e60-bf09-09080bfcb230" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-233b7b4b-69d5-40ee-c53c-f22134bfb2c2"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="053e2885-627e-4ec4-9fc8-4a950065c4ca"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="7671038" change-id="32743286-558f-421a-a869-bc251723d967" timestamp="1644576419180"?>The definition of age of majority, i.e., when an individual is considered to be a “minor” varies within Canadian jurisdictional domains at both the federal and provincial/territorial levels of jurisdictional domains. It also varies with respect to rights and responsibilities of both (1) the individual; and, (2) those of its parent(s) or guardian(s).<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="32743286-558f-421a-a869-bc251723d967"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4092f11f-7b26-4c7b-be2e-008bea409746" timestamp="1627510202636"?></p></fn></p></list-item></list><p/><list list-type="dash"><list-item id="id-d9e6a450-166c-46c2-eb00-3ade26ca3979"><p>certification that qualifies one to perform a certain job</p></list-item><list-item id="id-1568dc5b-facd-48ea-9505-d61c723a5dcc"><p>need for codes of conduct for online course with respect to information sharing by participants (e.g. via MySpace, Facebook, wikis, You Tube, blogs, etc.). “Best practices” in ITLET need to be more broadly promoted and implemented. These and related pedagogical issues could perhaps be supported by appropriate standards.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4092f11f-7b26-4c7b-be2e-008bea409746"?></list><p/></sec>
